 EXECUTIVE Secretary/CEO of the Nigerian Shippers’ Council, NSC, Barr. Hassan Bello, has said that intra-African trade stands the chance of rising by as much as $35billion per annum if the African Continental Free Trade Agreement, AfCFTA, is properly implemented. Continue reading AfCFTA: Intra-Africa trade may hit $35bn  — Shippers’ Council boss at Vanguard News. Source: Vanguard